Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Deputy Director, Beaumont Public Library/Bibliotheque de Beaumont Beaumont , AB Description The Bibliothèque de Beaumont Library is seeking a creative and strategic Deputy Director. This position leads and oversees all patron services, including programming, outreach, community engagement, digital literacy initiatives, membership, and circulation. As Deputy Director, you will have the unique opportunity to shape the direction of public library offerings in one of the fastest-growing communities in Alberta. The Deputy Director is a brand-new position designed to integrate all patron-facing services and explore new ways to meet community needs. Our Strategic Plan challenges us to expand our membership; seek out new partners in our community and beyond; incorporate creative technologies into programs and services; better understand our community through evidence-based investigation; and take seriously our obligation to Truth and Reconciliation and marginalized community members. Achieving these goals will require daring, innovative thinking, and strategic planning. WHAT WE'RE LOOKING FOR: As the ideal candidate, you are an experienced manager with exceptional relationship-building skills and a head full of ideas. You aren’t afraid to try new things and you know how to motivate and inspire your team and your community to be brave with you. You are a compassionate manager who knows how to get the best out of people by leading with curiosity. You understand the operational functions of a public library, and you know how to integrate services to create a seamless patron experience. For full position details, please see the complete job ad on our website. WHO WE ARE: The Library’s mission is to connect people to ideas, experiences, and one another. Guided by our values of connection, courage, fun, inclusivity, and respect, we strive to fulfill our vision to be a place for everyone to gather, explore, learn, and express themselves. For more information about the Beaumont Library, check out our website and Strategic Plan. QUALIFICATIONS AND EXPERIENCE: MLS/MLIS from an ALA-accredited programThree years of supervisory, leadership, management, or directly related experienceExperience building and maintaining relationships with community partnersExperience in planning, budgeting, project management, and evaluation COMPENSATION: $35.70 - $46.58 per hour; $64,974 - $84,776 yearly, generous benefits package HOURS OF WORK: permanent full-time, 35 hours/week, flexible scheduling, work-from-home options CLOSING DATE: September 5, 2023, at 5:00 PM MST TO APPLY: Please email a cover letter and resume to Laura Winton, laura@beaumontlibrary.com. Only candidates who are selected for an interview will be contacted. Compensation $64,974 - $84,776 yearly Closes: 5 September, 2023 Beaumont Public Library Beaumont , AB Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
