ons. You will also be required to satisfactorily complete a Criminal Record Check (Working with Children &amp; Vulnerable Adults).Please submit your resume and cover letter to: hr@virl.bc.ca referencing Job Posting GEU2023-59 CR in the subject line of your email.Applications will be accepted until Saturday, September 2nd, 2023 at 5:00 pm.This is a (Permanent) BC GEU Unionized position providing an hourly rate of $35.34 - Visit our job board for additional details at: CSL, Child &amp; Youth.VIRL thanks all applicants for their interest in working with us however only those selected for an interview will be contacted directly. Compensation $35.34 per/hr Closes: 2 September, 2023 Vancouver Island Regional Library Campbell River , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
