Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Operations &amp; Records Management Supervisor Burnaby , BC Description Who We AreAt BCIT, putting people at the core of everything we do is paramount. This idea is the foundation of BCIT’s People Vision, which describes the Institute’s goals and priorities in respect to our people. In a complex and uncertain world, it’s vital our people feel valued, supported and connected. BCIT champions a culture of innovation and global progress through people’s imagination and creativity. With a competitive compensation package, great work-life balance, and career advancement opportunities, see why we’ve earned the title of one of BC’s Top Employers for over ten years running.Position SummaryBCIT’s Library Services department is seeking a temporary, part-time (0.8 FTE) Operations &amp; Records Management Supervisor. The Operations &amp; Records Management Supervisor supports the Operations Manager and the Director, Library Services, and supervises the daily operations of Records Management and the library administration office. Administers the provision of confidential administrative, financial and logistical operational matters for all campus libraries, oversees assistance in information services, including Records Management, Copyright, Reference, and Archives.DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES:Supervises the day-to-day operational support of the Library Administration office, and oversees and assigns work to the Operations &amp; Records Management section, ensuring the team maintains current knowledge of records management by keeping up-to-date with current practices, reference tools, and resources through in-house and external continuing education. Oversees the preparation and delivery of one-on-one and group training sessions on records management in person and online. Administratively manages attendance and makes certain that recording follows policy, and that all related records and reports are submitted to Payroll and/or Human Resources. Participates as a member of the library supervisory team; collaborates with colleagues, ensuring efficient and effective delivery of library services; maintains awareness of the Manager’s and the Director’s goals and objectives, establishing priorities and identifying items requiring attention. Ensures administrative and logistical support for Director-level meetings; manages and coordinates resources required for leadership team library events.Acts as Records Custodian of the Library Services Administration office, annually reviewing series inventories, creating and discarding files according to established policy and procedures. Coordinates and provides support and advice to departmental records custodians across the institute, confirming proper management of paper records and electronic repositories, off-site records program, and disposition of records, ensuring legal compliance. Oversees the retrieval and refiling of inventory from off-site storage locations. Oversees Archives support, including responding to reference queries, processing requests, and digitizing documents as required; coordinates with the Archivist and/or the Collections Librarian to accept archives donations; accessions records; processes archival holdings and oversees the identification and preservation of historical records; manages vital records control.Prepares and consults with Operations Manager regarding annual review of disaster prevention plan and recovery procedures for the department. Prepares budget analysis, tracks financial transactions and expenditures, and reconciles and submits monthly statements; communicates with Financial Services and coordinates submission of various reports. Participates in the assessment of renewal and new records management and shredding vendor contracts; coordinates with Financial Services and Corporate Services on processes related to Access Copyright contracts; liaises with Information Technology Services to troubleshoot Records Management and Copyright Tracking database issues, and suggests programming changes. Oversees building walk-throughs, ensuring cleaning standards are maintained and building deficiencies are reported and addressed by Facilities Services department. Reviews submissions for operational requisitions (e.g., furniture, equipment, supplies, systems, and maintenance) and oversees related delivery logistics.Coordinates the scheduling of Research Help Desk support, ensuring operational effectiveness and service delivery.Supports, plans and reports out on employee engagement activities; develops content for internal communications. Participates in and supports department recruitment activities as required.Prepares and maintains Library statistics for provincial and national surveys.Occasional travel may be required. Performs related duties as assigned.QUALIFICATIONS:Definition:The qualifications section for this position was developed using the approved job evaluation plan, agreed to between the BCGEU and BCIT. The qualifications represent the minimum qualifications required in the future (i.e. to be reflected in job postings) and do not reflect the incumbent’s existing qualifications.Education: Completion of Grade 12, plus completion of a two-year accredited Library and Information Technology Diploma. Requires a certificate in Records Management.Experience:Two years’ general experience plus six years’ practical, current experience in a similar position in a library or records management setting including 4 years of supervisory and leadership experience.Software/Computer Application(s) and Expertise:Considerable knowledge of and experience with advanced features of Microsoft Office applications such as Word, Excel, PowerPoint and Outlook.Working knowledge in a variety of software programs, databases, web browsers, web editing software and Adobe Acrobat.Knowledge of and experience with records management systems.Communication/Interpersonal Skills:Excellent organizational, interpersonal, oral and written communication skills.Ability to deal courteously, tactfully, and discretely with clients in a diverse and inclusive environment.Excellent problem-solving and decision-making skills.Administrative Skills (e.g. prioritizing, minute taking, wp speed, etc.):Demonstrated ability to set priorities, manage deadlines and details, coordinate multiple tasks, undertake and monitor project initiatives, while exercising considerable judgment, tact and diplomacy.High level of accuracy.Other Skills/Abilities:Demonstrated ability to deal with confidential matters in accordance with accepted professional and ethical standards.Proven ability to work effectively in a customer-service oriented, team environment. Ability to carry out physical requirements of the position (e.g., lifting boxes of up to 35 lbs). Benefits – Why you’d love working with usCompetitive payMinimum of fifteen days of vacationCompetitive employer-paid extended health and dental plan – take a look at our benefit plans!Defined benefit pension plan with employer contributionsFlexible hybrid work arrangements availableProfessional Development funds and resourcesAccess to most BCIT Flexible Learning courses free of chargeWellness and Employee Assistance programsComplimentary membership with free access to the Fitness Centre, Gymnasium, and moreBCIT values diverse experiences, ideas, cultures and perspectives and is committed to fostering a diverse and inclusive workplace. As an equal opportunity employer, we encourage applications from members of all groups experiencing barriers to equity. If you require accessibility accommodations during any part of the application or hiring process, please contact RecruitmentAssistant@bcit.ca so we can best support you. Please note that all applications must be submitted via the careers page portal, email applications will not be accepted.The British Columbia Institute of Technology acknowledges that our campuses are located on the unceded traditional territories of the Coast Salish Nations of xwməθkwəy̓əm (Musqueam), Sḵwx̱wú7mesh (Squamish), and səl̓ilwətaɁɬ (Tsleil-Waututh).To view the full posting, and to apply, please visit: https://careers.bcit.ca/postings/7510 Compensation $57,937 per annum. Closes: 20 November, 2023 British Columbia Institute of Technology Burnaby , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
