patrons through all mediums are high-quality, efficient and effective.Evaluates communication to ensure consistency, quality and relevance.Participates in the development of the Library’s Capital and Operating Budgets and manages the associated budgets related to marketing and communications.Identifies trends in service delivery, and uses statistics and other metrics for the purpose of short, medium and long-term planning.Participates in the development and achievement of goals and objectives for the Milton Public Library.Works co-operatively with the Leadership and Management Teams to assess needs and develop plans to support library operations and the achievement of goals.Actively participates in networking and community partnerships and on external and internal committees and attends meetings, courses and conferences as required.May serve as a management representative on various committeesParticipates in publicity, community relations, and special projects and events.Attends and participates in Library Board meetings as requiredPerforms other duties as assigned.Qualifications:University Degree in Marketing, Communications, Public Relations, Journalism or related discipline. Minimum four (4) years’ of Management experienceDemonstrated supervisory experience in a union environmentHighly developed oral and written communication skillsSuperior facilitation and interpersonal skillsKnowledge of development in library field and relevant legislationProven ability in managing changeWork EnvironmentWorks to frequent deadlines in a fast-paced environmentWorks at any MPL library location or offsite as necessaryPart-time including evenings and weekends, as required.Supervises in a unionised workplaceDirect ReportsMarketing &amp; Communications Assistant Application ProcessInterested candidates are asked to submit a resume and covering letter indicating how they meet the qualifications of this position by 5:00 pm on September 1st, 2023 quoting posting 23-20 to:Human Resources