Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? 23-19 District Teacher Librarian. Aiyansh , BC Description Nisga'a School District 924702 Huwilp Road, PO Box 240 New Aiyansh, BC V0J 1A0Phone: 250-633-2228Fax: 250-633-2401Competition #23-19EMPLOYMENT OPPORTUNITYDistrict Teacher Librarian Nisga’a School District No. 92 Nisga’a School District No. 92 invites applications for a District Teacher Librarian. This is a full time position starting September 1, 2023Nisga’a School District is located in the majestic and breathtakingly beautiful Nass valley in northwestern British Columbia. The district encompasses the traditional treaty territory of the Nisga’a Nation along the Nass River. People from around the world are drawn to Nisga’a lands to experience diverse outdoor explorations, including the volcano, Lava Bed Park, natural hot springs, fishing, hiking, hunting, kayaking/canoeing, biking, sledding, etc., as well as to encounter Nisga’a culture.The Nisga’a School District is currently partnered with the Harvard Graduate School of Education through the Deeper Learning Dozen community of practice which is seeking to radically transform education for more equitable outcomes for students. We are also partnering with MIT’s Learning Lab, working with Peter Senge and Mette Boll on building compassionate learning systems. Together, these initiatives provide an exclusive leading edge in professional learning that links system transformation, place-based learning, embedding Nisga’a language, culture, knowledge and worldviews, and truth and reconciliation. with exceptional instructional practice.If you are interested in joining our journey, you will engage in unparalleled opportunities and experiences that will enrich you personally and professionally.Additional incentives: Moving allowance Rent rebates/subsidies, furnished, affordable housing ($350 to $600 depending on size) Competitive salary ($61,942 to 111,226) Recruitment and Retention allowance for all teachers ($2947 paid over 10 months of the school year, based on FTE). Isolation Allowance for our remote communities: Laxgalts’ap - $2,336; Gingolx - $4,030 Mentoring and coaching for new teachers. This position is eligible for a pre-employment signing bonus of 10,000 in return for a successful candidate accepting a job offer for this position.
The successful candidate will have demonstrated: Appreciation for the key role that Language and Culture play in Indigenous Education Experience and formal training as a Teacher Librarian in the K-12 system Knowledge of library cataloguing systems and building and managing resource collections Ability to support classroom teachers in research and unit planning Technology skills necessary to run modern libraries Care, compassion, and learner-focused practices Appreciation for the key role that Language and Culture play in Indigenous Education Commitment to working as part of a team to develop and implement individualized learning plans with academic, behavioral, and social-emotional goals Respect for diversity, strong interpersonal skills, and an inquiry-based mindset The ability to positively engage with and motivate students Respect for and encouragement of meaningful parent involvement in school Demonstrate strong classroom management Commitment to collaboration and teamwork Willingness to encourage and challenge students in a culturally rich environment Competence in implementing the BC Curriculum, including current pedagogical and assessment practices Personal commitment to learning
Qualifications and Experience: Valid BC Ministry of Education Teaching Certificate (or eligible for). Be legal to work in Canada Committed to following the goals and strategies outlined in the school and district framework for enhanced learning. Working knowledge of the learning standards, curricular competencies, and core competencies within the BC Curriculum.
To view the original posting, please visit Make a Future at https://bit.ly/3KLfHIz. Should you have any questions regarding this posting, please contact our Human Resources Department.Please include a resume and cover letter including three work related references to the Human Resource Department @humanresources@nisgaa.bc.ca. Open until filled. Compensation ($61,942 to $111,226) Closes: 16 September, 2023 Nisga'a School District 92 Aiyansh , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
